<figureCitation box="[952,1036,838,863]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1777,1800]" captionTargetBox="[180,1411,261,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,238,1718]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Ruppeliana signiceps (Stål, 1862). 28 – 33, body, dorsal view: 28, female holotype (total length 9.5 mm) of Tettigonia signiceps from Rio de Janeiro State (NHRS); 29, male holotype (t. l. 8.7 mm) of T. coronulifera Stål, 1862 syn. nov. from Rio de Janeiro State (NHRS); 30, male holotype (t. l. 8.7 mm) of T. taschenbergi Berg, 1899 syn. nov. from Brazil (MLUH); 31, female (t. l. 9.2 mm) from Minas Gerais State previously identified by D. A. Young as R. coronulifera (MHNP); 32, male (t. l. 8.4 mm) from Rio de Janeiro State previously identified by G. Mejdalani as R. coronulifera (MNRJ); 33, male (t. l. 8.5 mm) from Minas Gerais State (MNRJ). 34, sternite VII of the holotype of T. signiceps, lateral view. 35, aedeagus of the holotype of T. coronulifera, lateral view (modified from Young 1977, fig. 611 f). Figs. 29 – 31 modified from Wilson et al. (2009); antennae and legs not depicted." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1005230/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
