<typeStatus box="[151,249,1054,1079]" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[291,425,1055,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tettigonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signiceps">
<emphasis box="[291,425,1055,1078]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">T. signiceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(anterior dorsum), male 
<typeStatus box="[713,811,1054,1079]" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[853,1022,1054,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tettigonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coronulifera">
<emphasis box="[853,1022,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">T. coronulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(anterior dorsum and genitalia) and male 
<typeStatus box="[212,310,1090,1115]" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berg" authorityYear="1899" box="[347,517,1090,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tettigonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taschenbergi">
<emphasis box="[347,517,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">T. taschenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(anterior dorsum only, the abdomen was missing); he also designated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[1304,1434,1091,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tettigonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signiceps">
<emphasis box="[1304,1434,1091,1115]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">T. signiceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[233,281,1127,1151]" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName box="[421,550,1126,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Ruppeliana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[421,550,1126,1151]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">Ruppeliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We believe that specimens previously associated with these three nomina (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[160,264,1163,1186]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tettigonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signiceps">
<emphasis box="[160,264,1163,1186]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">signiceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[280,419,1162,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tettigonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coronulifera">
<emphasis box="[280,419,1162,1187]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">coronulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berg" authorityYear="1899" box="[485,628,1162,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tettigonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taschenbergi">
<emphasis box="[485,628,1162,1187]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">taschenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) belong to a single species that has a somewhat variable color pattern (
<figureCitation box="[159,297,1198,1223]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1777,1800]" captionTargetBox="[180,1411,261,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,238,1718]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Ruppeliana signiceps (Stål, 1862). 28 – 33, body, dorsal view: 28, female holotype (total length 9.5 mm) of Tettigonia signiceps from Rio de Janeiro State (NHRS); 29, male holotype (t. l. 8.7 mm) of T. coronulifera Stål, 1862 syn. nov. from Rio de Janeiro State (NHRS); 30, male holotype (t. l. 8.7 mm) of T. taschenbergi Berg, 1899 syn. nov. from Brazil (MLUH); 31, female (t. l. 9.2 mm) from Minas Gerais State previously identified by D. A. Young as R. coronulifera (MHNP); 32, male (t. l. 8.4 mm) from Rio de Janeiro State previously identified by G. Mejdalani as R. coronulifera (MNRJ); 33, male (t. l. 8.5 mm) from Minas Gerais State (MNRJ). 34, sternite VII of the holotype of T. signiceps, lateral view. 35, aedeagus of the holotype of T. coronulifera, lateral view (modified from Young 1977, fig. 611 f). Figs. 29 – 31 modified from Wilson et al. (2009); antennae and legs not depicted." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1005230/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">Figs. 28–33</figureCitation>
). All females have a similar sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[758,840,1198,1223]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1777,1800]" captionTargetBox="[180,1411,261,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,238,1718]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Ruppeliana signiceps (Stål, 1862). 28 – 33, body, dorsal view: 28, female holotype (total length 9.5 mm) of Tettigonia signiceps from Rio de Janeiro State (NHRS); 29, male holotype (t. l. 8.7 mm) of T. coronulifera Stål, 1862 syn. nov. from Rio de Janeiro State (NHRS); 30, male holotype (t. l. 8.7 mm) of T. taschenbergi Berg, 1899 syn. nov. from Brazil (MLUH); 31, female (t. l. 9.2 mm) from Minas Gerais State previously identified by D. A. Young as R. coronulifera (MHNP); 32, male (t. l. 8.4 mm) from Rio de Janeiro State previously identified by G. Mejdalani as R. coronulifera (MNRJ); 33, male (t. l. 8.5 mm) from Minas Gerais State (MNRJ). 34, sternite VII of the holotype of T. signiceps, lateral view. 35, aedeagus of the holotype of T. coronulifera, lateral view (modified from Young 1977, fig. 611 f). Figs. 29 – 31 modified from Wilson et al. (2009); antennae and legs not depicted." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1005230/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
, see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[947,1087,1199,1223]" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, i - vi + 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977">Young 1977</bibRefCitation>
: 748, fig. 609i) and males have the aedeagus as illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[485,639,1235,1259]" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, i - vi + 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977">Young (1977)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[685,852,1234,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tettigonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coronulifera">
<emphasis box="[685,852,1234,1259]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">T. coronulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[867,950,1234,1259]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1777,1800]" captionTargetBox="[180,1411,261,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,238,1718]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Ruppeliana signiceps (Stål, 1862). 28 – 33, body, dorsal view: 28, female holotype (total length 9.5 mm) of Tettigonia signiceps from Rio de Janeiro State (NHRS); 29, male holotype (t. l. 8.7 mm) of T. coronulifera Stål, 1862 syn. nov. from Rio de Janeiro State (NHRS); 30, male holotype (t. l. 8.7 mm) of T. taschenbergi Berg, 1899 syn. nov. from Brazil (MLUH); 31, female (t. l. 9.2 mm) from Minas Gerais State previously identified by D. A. Young as R. coronulifera (MHNP); 32, male (t. l. 8.4 mm) from Rio de Janeiro State previously identified by G. Mejdalani as R. coronulifera (MNRJ); 33, male (t. l. 8.5 mm) from Minas Gerais State (MNRJ). 34, sternite VII of the holotype of T. signiceps, lateral view. 35, aedeagus of the holotype of T. coronulifera, lateral view (modified from Young 1977, fig. 611 f). Figs. 29 – 31 modified from Wilson et al. (2009); antennae and legs not depicted." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1005230/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
); sternite VII has a posteromedian lobe and the aedeagus has very elongate and slender atrial processes. In order to prevent further confusion, we believe that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tettigonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coronulifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">T. coronulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berg" authorityYear="1899" box="[344,516,1306,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tettigonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taschenbergi">
<emphasis box="[344,516,1306,1331]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">T. taschenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered as synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[947,1082,1307,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tettigonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signiceps">
<emphasis box="[947,1082,1307,1331]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="446">R. signiceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
